  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH officer UNHCR Kosti, Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Due drought in Sudan, there are increased and urgent needs in the refugees camps particularly within the WASH sector.There are 9 refugee camps in White Nile hosting over 172,000 refugees from South Sudan. Camps are congested and there is need to establish another camp to decongest the existing camps, as well as to have additional space for accommodating new arrivals. Access to water and water closet is very low.Currently, only 11.8 liters/person/day is available against 25 liters/person/day of Sudan&apos;s standard for rural areas. Water systems in all camps need to be rehabilitated/upgraded. There is no adequate WASH technical capacity at the State level. Therefore, there is need to increase the WASH technical capacities to be able to meet the need to improve the WASH situation in the existing camps and to establish new camps in future and capacity building of the local technical teams.The WASH Officer will support the UNHCR Kosti Operation to plan, execute and coordinate WASH activities at the State level and to improve the WASH situation in the White Nile State camps and host communities. The incumbent will also build the capacity of the UNHCR and partner technical staffs.</narrative>
  </description>
